    "comment": "Rationale: Pre-embedding immuno-peroxidase labelling for electron microscopy indicates the presence of Alpha2A Adrenergic receptor (Alpha2A-AR) immunoreactivity in some dendrites and spines in the hippocampus (Fig. 3, 4, 6, 8, 9). Immunoreactive postsynapses were \"exclusively asymmetric contacts\". Alpha2A-AR immunoreactivity was often intense at the postsynaptic density and perisynaptic region (figure legend Fig. 3).\n\nPreabsorption of the antibody with the peptide completely abolishes immunostaining (Fig. 1C).. Experimental description: Fourteen adult male Sprague-Dawley rats (250-300 g;Hilltop Labs, Scottdale, PA) were used in the study.",
